text.text:
I've been coming here regularly for a couple weeks now and I've had a great experience every time. It's a great place to relax, socialize, or focus on some work. The workers are great & friendly, the coffee is amazing, and the cats are simply the cutest.

They've done such a great job creating a welcoming and pleasant environment. Make sure you stop by!

This was my first experience with a cat cafe and I'm glad I chose this place. Prices were fair and proceeds all go to helping these cats live their best lives and find good homes. And the merch was crazy, if you want ideas for how to promote your business,this is the place to go. They had paintings, earrings, clothes, mugs, and basically everything cat related thing you can think of. 10/10 would gladly come here again.

Had such a great time here, the staff and cats are so lovely and friendly. Staff know the cats well and care for them dearly. We visited during zen hours and some of the cats were sleeping whilst others were happy to play and interact, so it was the best of both worlds. Watch out if you bring food into the cat lounges, cutie Red was very eager to try and get a bite of pumpkin muffin! I'm visiting from another country but I don't think I could have resisted adopting if I lived in Indy! Thank you guys for an amazing experience and for all you do for your animals. :)

What a relaxing and enjoyable eating experience!  My wife and I stopped in  Saturday morning recently and really enjoyed the food and coffee.  The owner greeted us and explained items on the menu.  Food is made from scratch and the coffee is incredible.  Up front seating is comfy and there is a smaller area at the back with couches and a coffee table.  The orange zest cream cheese cake we had for dessert was amazing.  Highly recommend if you're looking for a different atmosphere or want to try something new in the area.

This place is quite the gem. Feels like home away from home - the atmosphere is laid back and friendly from the moment you enter. The staff are INCREDIBLE people and we've gotten the pleasure of getting to know the family that owns + operates it. The food is always delicious and fresh. They are constantly changing things up seasonally. The baked goods are phenomenal - we love their Groovy Cat Cake and have done several custom baked goods orders with them. Check this spot out, it'll be sure to brighten up your day.

Unique and much needed cafe for this area. Had a quick work meeting here with a latte and then got their quiche of the day w greens on the side. Sooo good! Menu is healthy with unique options for breakfast/lunch and fresh baked goods as well. Highly recommend this cute spot!

This is a great way to get to meet the adoption cats. Great little place staff is very friendly, so we're the cats and kittens if you recently lost your fur family  member. This is a place where you can meet the cat or cats and play with them. Lunch was good. I highly recommend  stopping by  it will ease the loss of your fur family member, but also comfort you in adopting  the next fur family member to make new memories with. Stop in

We drove an hour and fifteen minutes to visit this very nice cat cafe. My expectations were surpassed big time. The staff, food and drink, and of course the main purpose the best kittens and cats you‚Äôve ever seen and played with. We had a great time. This place does not smell like chemicals and pet poop. It feels like you are visiting a cat spa. If its soul purpose is to help you forget your troubles then it worked. We did not go to adopt, we went to see the kitties. Sometimes you go to places and you feel like ‚Äú been there done that‚Äù I feel the opposite. This will be on my list of staycations every year. We each had some very tasty coffee and pastries before we hung out with our new furry friends. Some great things I noticed.
1. The cats wear collars. Our cat will not wear a collar because she never got used to it. Important for identification in case your cat gets lost.
2. No pushy sales, Not once did someone try to guilt us into adopting.
3. Every cat or kitten is around other cats and kittens. So if we decide to adopt down the road we know the issue with your pet and your new cat should go smooth as can be.
Sorry about this long review but this place is damn near perfect.

What an adorable place! Everywhere you look is cat themed sayings on the wall or cat decor on the tables... but so well put together and not tacky! I want to try every drink and every food item because it all sounds delicious.  (Nutty pumpkin latte? Yes please!) Upstairs you can view the cats from a birds eye view and play cat themed games or look through cat themed books.

If you want to pet the kitties it's $11/pp and is for 50 minutes with entry at the top of the hour (10 ppl at a time). We'll definitely be back for that sometime.

So glad we got to come visit.  We were out this way and happen to be looking for a place to sit down for a cup of coffee.

Wish Google would include them when searching coffee though... it doesn't come up and is the best in the area for a great cup of joe!

cafes.name: Btown Meow Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 5015 IN-46 Unit H, Bloomington, IN 47404, USA

text.text: This is my favorite local spot in Bloomington! The owners are fantastic and truly care about every cat that comes through their door; they partner with the animal shelter, and the folks there also have nothing but good things to say about them. The space is great and the cats are treated so well, the drinks are tasty, and the merch is cute and cozy! Need to stop by again soon. :)

Absolutely love this place. So inviting and just overall fun! The cats are all up for adoption and there is always a mixed bag of personalities. The drinks they serve are delicious and moderately priced as well. If you haven‚Äôt given this place a try nows the time!

What a great place to enjoy some activities or stop in for a drink! The cats are always great entertainment. I don‚Äôt know how they do it, but it‚Äôs always clean and well taken care of inside. Such a great addition to our area and I believe it really does help socialize the cats.

cafes.name: The Cat‚Äôs Closet
cafes.address: 223 S Pete Ellis Dr Suites 1 and 2, Bloomington, IN 47408, USA

text.text:
This is such a neat place! I‚Äôm not one for vintage clothing so I honestly just went for the cats. We told the person at the desk that it was our first time coming in. They let us hang out with the cats at no cost which was so sweet of them. The cats are loveable, calm, and adorable. I would definitely come back & bring friends with me when I do!

& for the person that left a 1 star review- take that review with a grain of salt. Because if you look at their profile, they are simply not a happy person. This is an AWESOME business & experience.

My sister and I had the absolute best time hanging out with these kitties and can‚Äôt wait to come back. The staff were incredibly kind and we also found a few unique pieces in the store! Genuinely will be coming back every day‚ù§Ô∏è

Visiting The Cat's Closet was such a treat! The business is split into two separate sections: a vintage clothing store and a cat lounge. You can browse the clothing selection for no charge (just like a typical shop), but to enter the cat lounge, a reservation is recommended and you'll need to pay a small fee.

Their vintage clothing is in great condition, wonderfully well-organized, and very reasonably priced! I was also pleasantly surprised by how much of a plus-sized selection there was. And there's a rack dedicated to items with cats on them! There are dressing rooms you can use to try things on as well, which is always appreciated.

The cat lounge was absolutely lovely! Since I went on a Tuesday it was only $2 to enter for 30 mins (every other day of the week its $7 for 30 mins). I was there at the end of the day and loved how part of the lounge was just lit by holiday lights. There's also an adorable little TV and a collection of 90s/2000s movies on VHS you can watch! All of that combined with the adorable decor throughout the lounge made for a really wonderful ambiance.

The cats themselves are very friendly and all adoptable through Bloomington Animal Care and Control! They are clearly very well taken care of and have a little private back room away from people they can can access via cat door. There lounge also didn't have any unpleasant odors, which is always nice! And there are little info sheets in the lounge where you can read about all the cats.

The owners were there when I visited and were both incredibly sweet! They were readily available and happy to answer any questions about the clothes or the cats.

It is worth noting that this isn't a cat caf√© in the sense that they don't sell any caf√© drinks. But there are plenty of other caf√©s in the area where you could grab something before or after visiting!  (Morgenstern's is a personal favorite of mine on that side of town.)

Overall, I loved this place! I will definitely be back to visit several more times and look forward to catching one of their events at some point!

cafes.name: Smitten Kitten Cat Cafe and Coffee Shop

text.text:
If you like cats, this is definitely a must for you. If you are looking to adopt or spend time with the felines. You will find cats of all sorts. If you want to relax there are chairs in the cat area and some of the cats may come up to you or you can play with them. The cats have a great amount of space to roam, hide, sleep, and play.

The food area is separate! Don't think you‚Äôll be eating where the cat plays. However, you can take your coffee with you into the cat area. The place is well taken care of and clean!

Kid's loved it. Tea wasn't bad. Did not eat anything, so I cannot comment but it looked good. The service was top notch. The cats seemed to enjoy the place as much as anyone else... Would recommend for cat lovers... and probably others.

Went to the Smitten Kitten in January with a couple friends and we absolutely enjoyed our visit! Seasonal drinks were tasty! Staff was friendly and answered all our questions! Nice clean environment to play with and interact with the cats! We‚Äôd gone in the afternoon, so the cats were a little sleepy, but still were able to interact and hang out! We‚Äôd definitely go again!

cafes.name: The Cat Lady Cafe South Bend
cafes.address: 401 E Colfax Ave Suite 104, South Bend, IN 46617, USA

text.text:
The Cat Lady Cafe is truly a special place. After losing our beloved dog of nearly 15 years, we were hesitant about bringing another pet into our lives. As self-proclaimed ‚Äúdog people,‚Äù the idea of adopting *cats*‚Äîand not just one, but two‚Äîseemed completely out of character. With young children and a busy lifestyle, a puppy simply wasn‚Äôt an option, but our seven-year-old had been asking for a cat for over a year. Meanwhile, our three-and-a-half-year-old, who is still learning to be gentle, made us cautious about introducing any new animals into the family.

We knew if we adopted, it would need to be a pair of littermates, and we had to be certain our youngest could handle the responsibility and respect the animals.

Enter the Cat Lady Cafe. Not only did they serve an excellent latte (and adorable ‚Äúcoffee‚Äù ‚Äî aka milk in coffee cups ‚Äî for the kids), but they gave us the perfect environment to observe our children‚Äôs behavior around cats. The cafe offered us a calm, cozy space to connect as a family and really consider what pet ownership would look like. We visited at least four times before making a decision. The mix of ensuring our kids were ready, finding cats with personalities that matched our family, and taking the time to think it through gave us the confidence to move forward.

Ultimately, we adopted two brothers‚Äînow named Goose and Maverick‚Äîwho are settling in beautifully and already quite spoiled! I believe the cats at Cat Lady Cafe are well-adjusted to noise and people, which has helped them socialize quickly in their new home.

Kim, the owner, clearly has both a vision and a passion for what she‚Äôs created here. I love that we were able to *adopt, not shop*, while supporting such a thoughtful and meaningful endeavor. The Cat Lady Cafe gave us not just two new furry family members, but also a sense of confidence that this was the right decision for us.

If you‚Äôre considering adoption or simply looking for a peaceful hour surrounded by cats, good coffee, and a welcoming environment, I highly recommend visiting. Goose and Maverick thank you, Kim!

We did not know what to expect when we entered, but we were surprised.
Let me first say, this place is very cute. The idea of a cat cafe is amazing in theory, but my issue is one thing and one thing only.

They charge you to actually interact with the cats. Which we found to be a turn-off.

It turns out this specific place is associated with the Humane Society. So what happens basically is you enter the cafe and are able to purchase food, drink and items if you choose.  There are some tables in the back to sit at if you would like.  The cats are in a separate room, there are windows all around so you can see them visually but they cannot be touched unless you pay to go in the room with them,  and it wasn't cheap in my opinion. They charge per person by the hour if I remember correctly.
I just remember when she told us the cost, there were 6 of us, and it was way too much to pay just to sit in a room with cats.
I would advise if this is something you're interested in doing to call in advance so you know what to expect.

I brought a friend here who loves cats. She really enjoyed this experience. You can pay a small fee to go in for an hour or a half hour. You are allowed to pet and play with the cats. They have merchandise and drinks for purchase. If you are looking for a relaxing interesting environment filled with cats this is the place for you.

cafes.name: Yellow Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 808 E Colfax Ave, South Bend, IN 46617, USA

text.text: We wanted to try a new breakfast spot, and we're extremely glad we tried Yellow Cat!  Cari was our waitress and she was fantastic!  Our coffees never went empty!  Everyone was super friendly and helpful.  Hot sauce selection is awesome.  Biscuits and gravey were delicious, and my friend had the farmer skillet and enjoyed it.  We will definitely be back!

A wonderful place to eat! And if you like '50s memorabilia, you love this place! Staff and customers are great, and the food is delicious! I wholeheartedly recommend!

This place has more than just great food.

A great spot for a hearty breakfast. A really nice community atmosphere right when you walk in. Really great portion sizes for very reasonable prices. The service was excellent and our waitress was very attentive and polite. The breakfast burrito was huge and very delicious. Their coffee is also really good! Definitely will return to try out more of their offerings.

cafes.name: Black Forest Cat Caf√©
cafes.address: 4716 Coldwater Rd, Fort Wayne, IN 46825, USA

text.text: Black Forest is an absolute gem and Fort Wayne is lucky to have them! The drinks are tasty, the atmosphere is cozy, and the staff are lovely. But the cats are the star of the show! The cat cafe space is spacious and there are so many ways to interact with the kitties on their terms. It‚Äôs also wonderful to see so many of these cats find a home from their time here. Well worth checking them out!
First time here! As an out of town visitor, I had a wonderful time at the cat cafe. The staff is friendly and considerate. The cat room is clean and odorless. The cats are all well-behaved ‚ù§Ô∏è

All around 10/10 place! The cats are adorable and the way the cats are in a separate room is super hygienic! It‚Äôs nice how you still can see the cats from the cafe area though!
The cats you can see by appointment and walk-ins as available. Last time I went it was $10 for a cat visit. I am not sure how much it is now.
The drinks are amazing and their espresso is NEVER burnt.
The special seasonal drinks are always rotating! Their everyday menu has great options too!
Their avocado toast is delicious and I recommend adding the bacon!
Also, if they have their s‚Äômores latte in season definitely give it a try, it is my favorite!

cafes.name: Cat Cafe - Kokomo Humane Society
cafes.address: 729 E Hoffer St, Kokomo, IN 46902, USA

text.text: I love this place! The cats seem well taken care of and the workers are always incredibly friendly. Coffee‚Äôs great too. I try to come here as much as my possible! The hours can be kinda weird but that‚Äôs totally understandable, since a lot of downtime and maintenance is necessary to keep these kitties happy and healthy.

what a lovely place!!! my boyfriend and i went just to get some coffees and visit the kitties, but now we‚Äôre seriously considering adopting one of them :-) i would definitely recommend making a visit to the cat caf√©. the drinks are inexpensive and very good. i recommend the caramel cinnamon chai with a shot of espresso. madison helped us and she was very kind and welcoming. this is a wonderful thing you guys are running, i wish more cities had something like this :-)

All 3 of our cats have come from here! They are absolutely amazing and have changed our lives for the better! We tried fostering a mom and baby and ended up falling in love and now we have the white one which we named, Baby!!

cafes.name: The Catmosphere LLC
cafes.address: 1287 Lafayette Ave, Terre Haute, IN 47804, USA

text.text:
It's a lovely place that is completely unique for the area. The cats are very sweet with unique personalities. There are lots of things to do with the cats and with other people. The games are fun, and there are plenty of different types of seating. I didn't try the caf√©, but the prices were very reasonable and the staff was lovely! I highly recommend and will definitely be returning!
I should also add that it was very clean and did not smell!

Catmosphere is a great place to go to for a relaxing day to hang out with cats. As a college student, I love to go on Sunday where they have a cheaper time allocated for college students and to wind down from all the constant work I have. Cats are constantly being adopted and new ones are being added in their place. Great place to look if you're willing to adopt as well.

It was such a fun time! They have separate area for the cats and the cafe areas. They have a selection of snacks, drinks, and sweets. You can go into the cat area for 30 minutes or an hour, depending on what time slot you pay for. The cats are all so sweet! We will be back to love on the cats soon!

Great goodness!! We reserved a spot right at 11, and for just a $10 reservation, we enjoyed up to an hour with the cats. From the moment we walked in, we were greeted by the sweetest cats and kittens. A delightful staff member joined us, sharing her knowledge about the adoption process and each cat in her care. It was the perfect midday break! We left with the same number of cats we arrived with‚Äîmuch to my husband‚Äôs relief.

If you‚Äôve been thinking about going but haven‚Äôt yet, do it! You won‚Äôt regret it. üêà  üêà‚Äç‚¨õÔ∏è

Enjoying life 1 sip, 1 bite, and 1 small town at a time! Explore everything!

love, Love, LOVE this place!! Visited from TN 8/17/24. Don't go in the late afternoon (2p-5p) because the "kids"(cats) are sleeping. We went at 4p and the majority of them were asleep. üòü A couple stirred, don't wake them. You go in a few at a time and there are double doors to make sure you don't let the "kids" out. Reservations are required. They have bottles of wine to buy, magnets, smoothies, snacks, pop and toys for the "kids". They ranged in age from a year to a 8 years old and you could adopt on the spot! They are well-behaved and each is named with their own personality. Nice part is you can have a conversations with lovely people who are of like mind and love domesticated, loving little kings and queens of your jungle!üëëüêà‚Äç‚¨õüêàüòªüòΩ

The coffee was okay. The macarons were amazing! But the kitties were the highlight of the day! The guy monitoring the cat lounge was very helpful and informative.

I do wish, however, that young children were limited or even not allowed to be in the room without someone responsible watching them. It kind of put a damper on our visit to have them chasing the cats off and being aggressive with them. They got scratched and bitten several times because they do not understand how to approach cats and their parent did nothing to correct or control them. She actually encouraged them to bother specific cats that we were clearly spending time with. At least one of the cats was visibly stressed the whole time they were in the room. I was happy to see them leave!

That was obviously a parenting problem, but the staff do need to set some boundaries or constantly be in the room to discourage this type of behavior and/or remove people from the room when needed.

Overall, I would definitely visit again! Maybe I‚Äôll just pay for all 10 spots to make sure we have a calm and pleasant experience. üòâ

cafes.name: Pawz Pet Cafe/Cat Cafe and boba tea

text.text: Such a fun place to visit! Stacia was so helpful, kind, and made some accommodations for one of our drinks :) the cats were so sweet, and were able to pet and spend time with quite a few. Lisa was also so very welcoming, and helpful! Will definitely be back again!!!

I stopped in to check out Pawz Pet Cafe.  They are still in their opening stages but I was impressed with the cat apparatuses they have for sale. You can adopt a cat and leave with all the goods.  I was especially impressed with the organic kitty litter they have for sale.  I‚Äôd definitely purchase that if/when we adopted a kitty.  Then I walked into the cafe portion.  I ordered a milk boba tea.  It wasn‚Äôt too sweet.  But they have tons of drink options and all reasonably priced.

Then I made my way into the kitty room. The set up is so cool! I was making a mental wishlist of things I wanted to get for my future kitty.  All of the cats there are super sweet and there is a booklet to learn more about each kitty available.

You do not need a reservation but it is advised. It‚Äôs $10 for 30 minutes to enjoy a drink and get to know some cats.  I can‚Äôt wait to take my boys soon.

Super cute coffee and kitten cafe! Rescued kitties are housed in a large playroom with lots of things to climb on and in and around. The staff knows each one and their personalities. Visitors have ample opportunity to adopt a new furry friend or just watch and love on them.
The coffee and snack bar has a great variety of specialty coffee drinks and teas. The baristas are outstanding.
You can also host a party here. Birthdays are super special, and everyone has a great time!

This was our second trip to Purrfect Day Cafe.  Both visits were for ~10 year old girl birthday parties.  I was skeptical at first, but this is an absolutely brilliant concept.
The dedicated ‚Äúpetting room‚Äù is full of 10ish kittens.  They are just at the age of being spayed/neutered. It‚Äôs a great way to acclimate the cats to people.  All cats are available for adoption.
My only complaint is the same thing as any Bardstown Road business.  Parking is horrible.
I don‚Äôt know how one-off visits actually work,  but I highly recommend checking this place out if you have the chance.

This is the most adorable coffee shop I‚Äôve ever been to, a pretty cool concept. You can go visit the cafe anytime but might need a reservation to see the cats/kittens depending on the day of the week.
Kittens galore, swag, great coffee drinks, and don‚Äôt even get me started on the adoptions eeekkk! Once you‚Äôve played with the kittens, you have the opportunity to take one or more home. It‚Äôs a very easy process and the kittens have already been fixed and vaccinated so you don‚Äôt even have to stop at the vet on the way home.

Check out their booking page, they have events that are great for girls and date nights. You can‚Äôt go wrong with the Purrfect Day Cat Cafe.

*This is the first cafe in the nation to reach and pass 10,000 adoptions since opening its doors. There‚Äôs magic in the Highlands, don‚Äôt miss out.

Absolutely amazing!! Whenever I visit a new city, I try to look for kitty cafes. Purrfect Day exceeded my expectations. The staff were so friendly and welcoming & the stars of the show (the 2-3 month old kittens) were soooooo cute and playful and cuddly. The room was clean, had plenty of toys and sleeping nooks for the kitties, was a great size and wasn‚Äôt overcrowded. I wish I could‚Äôve stayed all night!

I loved visiting Lucky Cat Cafe. There were about 12 cats when I visited and they were all so friendly. The cats were obviously very well taken care of and the establishment was very clean. I loved visiting with the cats and petting them all. The staff was very friendly and helpful. They have a cute little gift shop with great gifts for cat lovers.

Cute, older home turned into a non-profit cat lounge. The employees were all very kind and welcoming and the cats seemed incredibly well cared for. There's not much parking, and it does get a bit cramped inside when there's a lot of people but overall, it was definitely worth the visit!

A charming environment to visit with cats and meet new people. It's such a nice, clean, calm place where you can really play and snuggle each cat.we loved it and will be bringing all our out of town friends and family!

Finally got to try this place and it was delicious! Sadly, they are only open until 2pm so I‚Äôve never been able to get there before now. Wish they‚Äôd expand the hours on the weekends at least. But I‚Äôll definitely try to go back. It was very tasty and reasonably priced

I like this place.  Very good breakfast.  They serve it with plastic utensils and foam plates but that‚Äôs not an issue for me.  The food is very good.  It‚Äôs a nice place with friendly service.  Do I love eating off plastic and foam? No.  But the food and atmosphere is good enough that I really don‚Äôt care.  The world is different after COVID so I don‚Äôt mind.  I will be back.  And I‚Äôll get it to-go on occasion.
The pumpkin Gouda soup was delicious!  Mom had bean soup and said it was perfectly seasoned, delicious as well.  This was my first time stopping in but won‚Äôt be the last.

Such a wonderful place. Great coffee and treats, and best of all, you get to cuddle with cats. All the cats are up for adoption too, so if you're looking for a new furry friend, stop by. The owner is very friendly and gave us some good insights into the town.

My husband, daughter and I visited Dexter's to visit with cats.  Brittney is extremely friendly and told us about each cat in the room.  We loved meeting all of the cats and learning their stories.  We submitted an application for Coconut before we left and are hoping to adopt him.  We will definately be back to visit, have a coffee and play with the cats in the future!  It's a great way to spend some time in the afternoon, help cats and enjoy a tasty drink!

Absolutely wonderful! Company of cats and some really friendly folks while sipping on an espresso drink and munching on a pastery.
Plenty of seating in the main lobby as well as the cat room.  Parking in the back or on the street.
a minimal fee based in time to spend with the cats, proceeds go to assist in caring and finding homes for the darling felines. Gift cards are available, a small section of cat themed items.

Drinks are Fantabulous, staff is great, pasteries delectable and the cats are just swell.

So I really appreciate this cafe, it gives temporary homes for kitties looking for adoption without them having to be in a cage at a shelter.

That being said, I think the quality of care could be improved. The cats were a little dirty and their noses and eyes looked in rough shape.

There was one worker/volunteer that was on his steam deck in the cat lounge and only got up to roughly pick up the cats. Cats are not toys, the way this person picked up and handled the cats was very concerning and I hope there will be some accountability.

Like I said, the 3 stars are for the concept and I can tell that they care about the cats and getting them adopted.

But there needs to be stricter training and discipline involved. Employees/volunteers should be working (not playing games) and maybe helping clean the area and the cats. They should also not be handling the cats so violently.

Please address these issues for the sake of improving the quality of care for these cats.
I don‚Äôt live here, but my brother has some coupons for this place, and the cats are very cute and aren‚Äôt too shy. Good place to relax.

A friendly feline destination in downtown Lafayette, with cordial staff and a bright room of crepuscular kitties. The cats are sociable but sleepy depending on the personality and the time. You pay by the hour, which goes by fast, and can take water or soda into the cat room. Excellent for kids and/or if you‚Äôre considering adoption.  You can also grab some sweet nibbles. A wonderful station for cat lovers passing through town.

A purrfect way to spend a cloudy Sunday afternoon! Make a reservation in advance to make the most out of this visit, and be sure to pop by the cafe before entering the cat room at least 10 minutes before you enter the room of adorable and soft cats to pet and play with! Whether you‚Äôre enjoying a nice cold or hot beverage with your loved ones, this is the most clean cat facility I‚Äôve ever been to!
Easy access to free parking across the street and a calming atmosphere for everyone.
I would highly recommend checking this and other cat cafes who are either looking to
Adopt or simply to hang out with these incredibly happy felines in a clean and friendly atmosphere!

This was hands down the best experience ever. Our beloved cat of 14 years passed away last year and we were ready to welcome some new cats into our family. The setup is so calming for the cats, lots of places to sleep or hide or play. Music going. Not too many people in there at a time to overwhelm them.

We left with two (not the same litter) and they have bonded really well. Couldn‚Äôt be  happier !

If I could give them 100 stars I would! This cat cafe is incredible because you are hanging out with adoptable shelter cats. The cats are adorable, and so much fun. I loved every second of it! This was a huge dose of serotonin for me, and I am hopeful every single one of the cats finds their furever home soon! Highly recommend!

cafes.name: Central Purrk Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 401 Outlet Center Dr #260, Georgetown, KY 40324, USA

text.text: We visited on a Saturday morning for a Yoga with Cats event. For $20, we received a 45 minute yoga session, 15 minutes of Cat Lounge time, and a small drink. I chose the vanilla iced coffee, and it was delicious! The Cat Lounge area was well maintained, and the cats appeared to be very content. We enjoyed using the various toy options available to play with the cats, and they seemed to have a lot of fun with them. Definitely recommend checking this place out and booking ahead if you want to go inside the Cat Lounge (or to visit for an event). Maybe you‚Äôll even find a furry friend to take home!

Wonderful place! Cats are clearly well taken care of. Everyone is so sweet! Jennifer was the bubbliest thing ever. Michaella made great coffee with a big smile. Kayleigh is so much fun to sit and laugh with. Great place guys. Thank you and I'll be back!
I love going here! The service is great, and the kitties are so well taken care of! I'm so happy to have a place like this in our community!
